    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-11-15T19:17:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-11-15T19:17:00-05:00" n="81"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d81">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 81</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">398.18-BR/11–1551: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                            <gloss type="to">Certain Diplomatic Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d81fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_WGL1">George L.
                            Warren</persName> of the Refugees and Displaced Persons Staff of the
                        Bureau of United Nations Affairs and cleared by <gloss target="#t_UNE1"
                            >UNE</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_BNA1">BNA</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_SM1">S/M</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_UNI1">UNI</gloss>, <gloss
                            target="#t_ARA1">ARA</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_LUNA1">L/UNA</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>, and <gloss target="#t_GPA1"
                            >GPA</gloss>. Sent to the Embassies and Legations located in all
                        countries to be invited to the Migration Conference and repeated to
                        Geneva.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">plain</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">night letter</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-11-15T19:17:00-05:00"
                            >November 15, 1951—7:17 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>459. Belg Govt at US suggestion has invited 32 Govts to participate conference on
                    migration Brussels Nov 26. US will make major proposals for consideration by
                    conference. These proposals consist of: <list>
                        <label>a.</label>
                        <item>Draft resolution providing for estab “Provisional Committee for the
                            Movement of European Migrants”, and that Committee take such action as
                            may be directly related to the moving of migrants from certain European
                            countries having surplus population, elect officers etc., exercise
                            powers required to carry out its purpose, adopt a plan of operations,
                            appoint a director and staff and vest director with necessary powers to
                            carry out responsibilities entrusted to him.</item>
                        <label>b.</label>
                        <item>Plan of operations incl organizational arrangements and objectives and
                            proposals for financing budget of expenditures of Provisional Committee.
                            Primary objective is to move 115,000 persons in one year of operations,
                            who wld not otherwise be moved, at over-all cost of $34,000,000. US is
                            prepared to contribute $10,000,000 (exclusive of any reimbursements to
                            Committee for services rendered to US) providing all Govts agree to
                            provide funds, services or reimbursements <pb facs="0233" n="191"
                                xml:id="pg_191"/> adequate to meet approx proposed budget of
                            $34,000,000.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>Govt to which you are accredited has been invited to conference. Copies draft
                    resolution and plan of organizational and financial arrangements forwarded under
                    separate cover soonest.</p>
                <p>Request you advise <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> foregoing, supply
                    copies above when recd and request <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss>
                    that Govt Rep at conference be authorized sign provisional arrangements provided
                    proposals acceptable to Govt.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
